1
00:00:02,140 --> 00:00:03,170
Careful.

2
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:06,280
- Oh my, it's hot!
- It's hot!

3
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:12,480
Can't you do anything right?

4
00:00:14,190 --> 00:00:16,590
I'm the one who spilled it,
but why did you hit her?

5
00:00:16,760 --> 00:00:19,260
If she had served you properly,
you wouldn't have spilled it.

6
00:00:19,590 --> 00:00:22,490
It's so hot.
I’m worried my leg might be badly burned.

7
00:00:23,530 --> 00:00:24,760
Get out of the way.

8
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:25,830
It's so hot.

9
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:33,840
Chae Hwa Young.
This is just the beginning.

10
00:00:34,510 --> 00:00:38,310
I'm going to torment you,
grinding you down piece by piece.

11
00:00:38,910 --> 00:00:41,610
Just like when you came into my home
wearing the face of an angel,

12
00:00:42,180 --> 00:00:45,980
I'll wear the mask of Ma Seo Rin
and give you a taste of your own medicine.

13
00:00:57,100 --> 00:00:58,260
(Episode 52)

14
00:00:58,330 --> 00:00:59,330
Mrs. Yang.

15
00:01:00,170 --> 00:01:01,170
I'm so sorry.

16
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:03,870
What's this?

17
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:05,840
It was my fault.

18
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:09,270
I was the one who spilled it,
but you took the fall for me.

19
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:12,780
I'm sorry. Please put this on for now.

20
00:01:13,850 --> 00:01:17,450
I never thought I'd see the day
you'd treat me like this.

21
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:20,120
What is the world coming to?

22
00:01:20,850 --> 00:01:22,720
This is just too weird
for me to wrap my head around.

23
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:26,620
Seo Rin didn't even apologize
in situations like this?

24
00:01:27,530 --> 00:01:28,890
What kind of person were you, Ma Seo Rin?

25
00:01:40,370 --> 00:01:43,510
Manager Lee, get that bastard
who hurt Seo Rin...

26
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,310
out of the country now.

27
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:48,580
Yes, I'm already looking into
how to get him out of the country.

28
00:01:48,910 --> 00:01:53,020
But he has a long criminal record,
so he can't legally leave via the airport.

29
00:01:53,420 --> 00:01:56,290
- I'm looking into smuggling him out.
- Just hurry up.

30
00:01:56,820 --> 00:01:59,460
If you drag your feet and they catch on,
we're in big trouble.

31
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:02,560
Don't worry. I'll handle it
so you won't have to think about it again.

32
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:07,670
Darn it.

33
00:02:22,980 --> 00:02:24,780
Where did Seo Rin hide the evidence?

34
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,850
I have to find it.

35
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:29,650
I told you that I have evidence.

36
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:31,460
Right now, you can't get caught.

37
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:34,830
Once you have the proof,
you can turn her in yourself.

38
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,790
I have the evidence!

39
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,730
I must find that evidence at all costs.
Only then can I punish Chae Hwa Young.

40
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:50,740
Seo Rin.

41
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:55,050
Good grief, what is all this mess?
What are you doing?

42
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:58,020
Where's my sleep mask?

43
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,420
I said, where's my sleep mask?

44
00:03:00,490 --> 00:03:01,520
Goodness.

45
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,360
Here it is.

46
00:03:05,890 --> 00:03:06,890
It stings.

47
00:03:08,990 --> 00:03:11,630
Good. It should sting even more.

48
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,370
That looks like a bad burn.
Don't you need to go to the hospital?

49
00:03:14,730 --> 00:03:15,930
It's not that bad.

50
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:19,740
Here.

51
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:23,210
I couldn't sleep last night,
so I'm turning in early.

52
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:26,110
My head is all jumbled.

53
00:03:27,110 --> 00:03:28,850
Don't try to force yourself to remember.

54
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:31,680
It will come back to you naturally
when it's ready.

55
00:03:32,550 --> 00:03:35,390
Here. It's that brand new phone
you wanted.

56
00:03:35,390 --> 00:03:36,390
Use this.

57
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:38,760
I don't want a new one.
I want the one I was using.

58
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:40,530
I told you it broke, so I threw it out.

59
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:49,700
All right. You should rest,
especially after a day like today.

60
00:04:00,010 --> 00:04:01,450
Just you wait, Chae Hwa Young.

61
00:04:01,650 --> 00:04:03,180
I'm going to put you through torment.

62
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:10,090
Hong Ju, did you see that?
Seo Rin spilled soup on her mom's leg.

63
00:04:10,820 --> 00:04:13,360
Chae Hwa Young was hopping around,
screaming about how hot it was,

64
00:04:14,730 --> 00:04:16,590
and it was so satisfying to watch.

65
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:19,160
It was priceless.

66
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:20,430
I know, right?

67
00:04:21,230 --> 00:04:24,000
But Mom, since Seo Rin has amnesia,

68
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:26,040
- she doesn't even recognize me, right?
- Right.

69
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,270
It will probably take some time...

70
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:30,410
for her to return to work, right?

71
00:04:30,410 --> 00:04:31,710
Of course it will.

72
00:04:32,310 --> 00:04:35,350
I've only ever seen amnesia on TV.

73
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:37,820
It's wild seeing it in person, right?

74
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:38,880
But...

75
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,650
she seems just as much of a brat
as before.

76
00:04:43,990 --> 00:04:45,160
Then again,

77
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:48,990
in some ways,
it feels like her memory is back,

78
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:51,900
but in other ways, it doesn't.
It's just so odd.

79
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:55,470
There's something anxious in her eyes.

80
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:58,440
It's probably just from the accident.

81
00:04:58,570 --> 00:04:59,640
You think so?

82
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:02,910
That's why car accidents
are so terrifying.

83
00:05:09,050 --> 00:05:11,280
When did they say Seo Rin's phone
would be fixed?

84
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:13,990
She told them to get my phone fixed?

85
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:16,120
But she told me she threw it away.

86
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:19,260
I've asked them to repair it quickly.
Please be patient.

87
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,830
I'm sure we'll find out why
Seo Rin had an accident...

88
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:24,100
in the same place as Oh Jang Mi,

89
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:28,100
and when the two of them found out
about each other,

90
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:30,970
once we get to look inside
Seo Rin's phone.

91
00:05:32,070 --> 00:05:34,310
A person's phone is practically
their second self.

92
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:37,980
No! I have to find that phone
before Chae Hwa Young does!

93
00:05:44,580 --> 00:05:46,520
Seo Rin, why are you standing there?

94
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,650
I was trying to sleep, but I couldn't.

95
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:53,520
Seo Rin, are you looking for your pills?

96
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:56,830
Goodness, I can't believe you can't sleep
without your pills.

97
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:58,830
Did you just scold me?

98
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,300
Goodness, what's gotten into you?

99
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,670
Goodness! Seo Rin!

100
00:06:10,910 --> 00:06:14,910
Why can't I sleep without sleeping pills?

101
00:06:15,510 --> 00:06:19,020
Why did I turn out like this?
I wouldn't know!

102
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,620
Why did I end up like this?

103
00:06:24,020 --> 00:06:27,330
- This is all your fault, Mom!
- Seo Rin, that's enough!

104
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:29,890
I won't stop.
Why did you raise me this way?

105
00:06:30,060 --> 00:06:31,760
This is the fault
of the one who raised me.

106
00:06:31,930 --> 00:06:35,200
Why did you raise me
to need sleeping pills?

107
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:38,070
- Be quiet! Stop it!
- What's all this commotion?

108
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:40,770
- Father.
- Yes.

109
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:41,940
Grandfather.

110
00:06:42,210 --> 00:06:44,340
Why was my little sweetheart crying?

111
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:48,180
She was yelling and scolding me.

112
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:51,880
- Goodness, when did I ever?
- I heard everything!

113
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:54,520
She just got home from the hospital!

114
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:56,820
You should be comforting her,
not yelling at her.

115
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,360
Father...

116
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:02,090
It's alright. No more tears.
Go on inside now.

117
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:12,300
Come on, now. Go on. Let's go in.

118
00:07:27,890 --> 00:07:28,920
Tae Pyung.

119
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:31,860
Baek Ho. The day of the accident,

120
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,890
Jang Mi said "see you later" to me
before she left.

121
00:07:35,190 --> 00:07:36,190
What?

122
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:38,900
Anyway,

123
00:07:39,700 --> 00:07:40,770
I'll see you later, Tae Pyung.

124
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,800
You don't think...

125
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,070
she said it as if she knew
the accident would happen, do you?

126
00:07:48,110 --> 00:07:50,410
How could Jang Mi have possibly
predicted the accident?

127
00:07:50,610 --> 00:07:54,150
But it's weird, why would she look sad
when we see each other every day?

128
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:57,350
You're probably just seeing it that way
in hindsight.

129
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:01,390
Besides, the hit-and-run driver
is still out there,

130
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:04,260
- so try not to read too much into it.
- I know, but still.

131
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:08,460
I'm just so upset.

132
00:08:09,830 --> 00:08:11,430
I can't believe this happened to Jang Mi.

133
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:30,750
Actually, I've already been
to the accident scene.

134
00:08:31,220 --> 00:08:34,090
Really? But you must be so busy
with your work as a lawyer.

135
00:08:34,290 --> 00:08:35,750
The day of the car accident,

136
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:38,860
it seems Jang Mi was supposed
to meet someone.

137
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:39,890
What?

138
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:43,860
That's right. Jang Mi said she was going
to meet a friend that day.

139
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,960
She did? Which friend?

140
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:47,600
When I asked who,

141
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:50,430
she just said it was someone
a lot like her.

142
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:52,200
Who could that be?

143
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,370
We have to figure out who that was.

144
00:08:55,010 --> 00:08:58,380
And apparently, two people were injured
in the accident.

145
00:08:58,540 --> 00:09:00,140
- Two people?
- Yes.

146
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:02,510
The truck didn't just hit Jang Mi.

147
00:09:03,110 --> 00:09:04,320
It hit someone else, too.

148
00:09:04,420 --> 00:09:08,150
So, like a chain-reaction accident?

149
00:09:08,150 --> 00:09:09,250
I'm not sure.

150
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:11,720
First, I think I should check
the hospital's emergency room.

151
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,860
I need to find out what exactly
happened that day,

152
00:09:14,230 --> 00:09:17,730
and whether it happened while Jang Mi
was going to meet that friend.

153
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:20,030
Yes. I'll go with you.

154
00:09:24,570 --> 00:09:26,370
Maybe I should call Hwa Young.

155
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,540
Since Director Ma was in a car accident,

156
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:30,410
she must be so heartbroken.

157
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:34,710
Honey. What are you thinking
so hard about?

158
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:37,380
What?

159
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:39,950
It's nothing.

160
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:44,220
Gosh, I'm so exhausted.

161
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,360
You are?

162
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,060
Want me to make some coffee?

163
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:50,230
That'd be great.

164
00:09:50,530 --> 00:09:53,730
Gosh, you're so thoughtful
that you know what I need without a word.

165
00:09:54,470 --> 00:09:56,430
How could I not adore you?

166
00:10:08,050 --> 00:10:10,010
The person you're calling is unavailable.

167
00:10:10,010 --> 00:10:11,480
Connecting to voicemail...

168
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:14,390
Darn, I was hoping to at least
hear her voice.

169
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:17,790
Honey, is the coffee almost ready?

170
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:20,320
Oh, right...

171
00:10:20,460 --> 00:10:22,490
It's brewing right now.

172
00:10:26,330 --> 00:10:27,700
(Emergency Medical Center)

173
00:10:27,830 --> 00:10:28,830
Excuse me...

174
00:10:29,530 --> 00:10:32,600
This patient was brought into
the ER a few days ago.

175
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:33,840
Do you happen to remember her?

176
00:10:34,110 --> 00:10:37,270
Yes, I do. It was quite a scene that day.

177
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,910
Were there any other patients
besides her, by any chance?

178
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,750
Like someone who was brought in with her.

179
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:43,610
Someone brought in with her?

180
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:51,620
No, there wasn't anyone.

181
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,560
That's weird.

182
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:55,430
I could've sworn there was someone else.

183
00:10:55,430 --> 00:10:56,860
What are you talking about?

184
00:10:57,260 --> 00:10:59,930
- You think there was someone else?
- Was there someone or not?

185
00:11:02,330 --> 00:11:03,330
No, there was no one else.

186
00:11:09,310 --> 00:11:12,440
Father, did you get rid of
Seo Rin's admission records?

187
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,480
Deleting admission records is illegal.

188
00:11:16,580 --> 00:11:18,520
- Then...
- I had them set to private.

189
00:11:19,180 --> 00:11:22,490
I also changed her name to an alias,
kept the medical staff to a minimum,

190
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:25,960
and made sure nothing was leaked,
even within the hospital.

191
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:27,790
That's a relief.

192
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:30,730
Thanks to your quick thinking,

193
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:34,330
Seo Rin's condition won't get out
to the press.

194
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:37,640
I've summoned Manager Lee.

195
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:39,470
Pardon?

196
00:11:41,370 --> 00:11:43,110
Fire Manager Lee.

197
00:11:43,670 --> 00:11:46,840
Fire Manager Lee? What do you mean?

198
00:11:47,210 --> 00:11:48,910
Manager Lee is one of my people.

199
00:11:49,010 --> 00:11:51,980
I let Manager Lee stay by your side...

200
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:56,520
because I trusted him
to protect you and our Seo Rin.

201
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:59,320
But just look at the state
our Seo Rin is in now.

202
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:01,460
It was an unavoidable accident.

203
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,560
It only happened
because Seo Rin snuck out...

204
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:06,530
That's the very reason I called you here.

205
00:12:07,830 --> 00:12:11,670
Why on earth were you having
Seo Rin watched?

206
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:16,510
Why did she pretend to be asleep
and sneak out of the house?

207
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:20,880
It's because Seo Rin has been
going out drinking lately,

208
00:12:21,050 --> 00:12:23,480
skipping work, and acting recklessly.

209
00:12:35,490 --> 00:12:36,560
This isn't going to work.

210
00:12:37,330 --> 00:12:41,000
If you do that, San Wol and Jin Hong Ju
will see through you in a second.

211
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:45,070
They are way too sharp.
They will realize you're not me.

212
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,840
What are you staring at?

213
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:55,350
Are you seeing me for the first time?

214
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:58,920
- No, it's just...
- What, is it a crime to look?

215
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,620
You're just trying to pick a fight.

216
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:02,920
That's because you were
giving me a nasty look.

217
00:13:15,970 --> 00:13:17,100
(Case Summary)

218
00:13:17,570 --> 00:13:19,570
He looks kind of familiar,

219
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,040
but I also feel like
I've never seen him before.

220
00:13:23,310 --> 00:13:24,410
I see what you mean.

221
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:28,350
I'm sure of it.

222
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:31,020
The man in the composite sketch
who bought the soju...

223
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:32,450
is Manager Lee.

224
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:35,220
What about the hit-and-run driver?

225
00:13:35,990 --> 00:13:38,590
Why haven't you caught the bastard yet?

226
00:13:39,420 --> 00:13:42,590
Why are you so protective of Manager Lee
when he's so incompetent?

227
00:13:43,230 --> 00:13:45,860
People who can replace him
are a dime a dozen.

228
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:47,870
Father, Seo Rin is my daughter.

229
00:13:48,630 --> 00:13:52,300
Don't you think I want to catch the person
who did this to my own daughter?

230
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,310
- I'm also doing my best...
- That's enough.

231
00:13:55,570 --> 00:13:56,570
You stay out of this.

232
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:58,780
Now, I'll be the one to catch...

233
00:13:59,110 --> 00:14:00,610
Seo Rin's hit-and-run driver myself.

234
00:14:00,610 --> 00:14:01,750
No...

235
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:04,750
I can't have Father
getting involved in this.

236
00:14:05,650 --> 00:14:07,150
What excuse can I give him?

237
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:18,560
You bastard!

238
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,850
Chairman, I deserve to die
for what I've done.

239
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:39,950
I'll gladly accept my punishment
for failing to protect Director Ma,

240
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:42,220
but if you give me just one more chance,

241
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:43,750
I'll make sure...

242
00:14:44,860 --> 00:14:46,460
this never happens again.

243
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:48,960
Grandfather!

244
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:52,530
- Please forgive Manager Lee.
- Seo Rin.

245
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:56,230
It's the hit-and-run driver's fault,
not Manager Lee's.

246
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,900
Please, make sure you catch the driver.

247
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:02,610
And when you do,
I'll tear them limb from limb.

248
00:15:02,810 --> 00:15:03,970
That's right, Seo Rin.

249
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:05,840
You were so terrified by the accident...

250
00:15:06,140 --> 00:15:07,750
that it even made you lose your memory,

251
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:09,210
so we have to make them pay for that!

252
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:10,750
Yes, Grandfather.

253
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:14,150
Manager Lee, it's not your time yet.

254
00:15:15,090 --> 00:15:18,460
To find out the truth,
I have to keep you close.

255
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,260
Once I find the proof,

256
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:22,790
I will not let you get away with this.

257
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:29,130
Jang Mi's gone. Tok Hee's gone.

258
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:32,200
Ok Hee, Tok Hee, and Bok Gil are gone.

259
00:15:33,770 --> 00:15:37,040
- Mom.
- Tae Sook, Jang Mi's gone.

260
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:38,680
Let's go to Jang Mi.

261
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:40,580
It's always about Jang Mi!

262
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:42,810
Please, just stop!

263
00:15:42,810 --> 00:15:44,050
It's always Jang Mi!

264
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:47,050
At least your favorite daughter
is lying in a hospital bed!

265
00:15:47,420 --> 00:15:49,450
I lost my dad!

266
00:15:49,790 --> 00:15:51,290
Ok Hee and Tok Hee...

267
00:15:51,290 --> 00:15:52,660
Jang Mi is hurt.

268
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:54,760
Tok Hee is hurt.

269
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,060
It's Baek Ho.

270
00:16:01,970 --> 00:16:06,670
Jang Mi is pretty. Tok Hee is hurt.
Let's go see our Jang Mi.

271
00:16:07,710 --> 00:16:10,170
- Ms. Jung.
- How am I supposed to live with her?

272
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:16,150
Jang Mi's gone.

273
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:18,980
Bok Gil's gone.

274
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:25,720
Ms. Jung.

275
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:29,060
Jang Mi is in the hospital right now.

276
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,900
She's just sleeping
because she's very tired.

277
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,770
If you just wait a little while,

278
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,270
she'll be right back by your side.

279
00:16:42,810 --> 00:16:46,410
Back to the mother
she loves more than anyone in the world.

280
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:50,280
Suk Hee likes Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

281
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:52,180
Jang Mi is pretty.

282
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:54,590
I love her.

283
00:17:01,390 --> 00:17:02,690
Do you...

284
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:04,830
want to give Jang Mi this doll?

285
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:06,700
Yes.

286
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:10,600
We just saw Jang Mi at the hospital
not too long ago, Mom.

287
00:17:10,870 --> 00:17:12,170
Just be patient.

288
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:15,110
That was Tok Hee.

289
00:17:15,910 --> 00:17:18,340
"Ok Hee, Tok Hee" then "Jang Mi,"
then "Tok Hee..."

290
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:20,440
I have no idea
what she's even talking about.

291
00:17:20,610 --> 00:17:23,750
She'll be in a regular room soon,
so please just wait a little longer.

292
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:26,920
I promise I'll take you
to see Jang Mi myself.

293
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,720
It's Tok Hee.

294
00:17:29,990 --> 00:17:30,990
Tok Hee.

295
00:17:31,490 --> 00:17:34,760
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

296
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:39,360
Are you saying
Oh Jang Mi got into a car accident?

297
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:43,830
Director Ma from my company
got into one today as well.

298
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:47,040
She was always such a nuisance.

299
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:50,010
Now that she's been in an accident,
I'm kind of worried.

300
00:17:51,210 --> 00:17:54,480
But how did Oh Jang Mi,
the woman Baek Ho likes,

301
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:56,010
get into an accident on the very same day?

302
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:07,620
- Hey, Jun Ho, what's up?
- Where are you?

303
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:10,530
You haven't been hanging around
Oh Jang Mi's hospital all day, have you?

304
00:18:11,230 --> 00:18:12,230
No, I haven't.

305
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,800
Why did you call?

306
00:18:13,930 --> 00:18:15,670
It's just that one of the directors
at my company...

307
00:18:16,170 --> 00:18:17,970
got into a car accident yesterday, too.

308
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,840
I was just wondering if it might have been
the same accident.

309
00:18:22,340 --> 00:18:24,610
Really? Who?

310
00:18:24,610 --> 00:18:25,710
Director Ma Seo Rin.

311
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:28,650
- CEO Chae Hwa Young's daughter.
- Ma Seo Rin?

312
00:18:29,350 --> 00:18:30,580
I met her at the reopening party...

313
00:18:31,050 --> 00:18:33,280
I remember her. The one who looks
just like Jang Mi.

314
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:36,520
Wait, but why would Jang Mi
be meeting Ma Seo Rin?

315
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:37,960
I'm not sure.

316
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:42,190
I doubt it.
She said she was meeting a friend.

317
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:44,560
Oh, I see.

318
00:18:45,530 --> 00:18:47,660
I just called on the off chance.

319
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,030
Listen.

320
00:18:49,330 --> 00:18:51,200
Don't get too wrapped up
in their family drama.

321
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:54,770
- Mom and Dad are worried.
- I can take care of myself.

322
00:19:12,690 --> 00:19:13,760
Chae Hwa Young.

323
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:16,630
You're my sworn enemy,

324
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:19,060
and I'm supposed to call you Mom?

325
00:19:22,670 --> 00:19:23,670
Right.

326
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:25,640
If I'm going to become Seo Rin,

327
00:19:26,370 --> 00:19:27,400
I have to.

328
00:19:29,370 --> 00:19:30,440
Mom...

329
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:33,410
I can't do it.

330
00:19:34,950 --> 00:19:37,180
How can I call the woman...

331
00:19:38,050 --> 00:19:42,590
who hurt my poor mother "Mom?"

332
00:20:12,650 --> 00:20:14,120
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

333
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,290
I told you to rest.
What are you doing here?

334
00:20:16,990 --> 00:20:18,020
Are you sure you're okay?

335
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:21,460
I'll be fine. This is nothing.

336
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:24,230
I'd be lost without you.

337
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:26,560
You know that, don't you, Kang Hyuk?

338
00:20:27,660 --> 00:20:28,900
Without you,

339
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:31,440
I wouldn't be able to live.

340
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:36,840
By the way, that old geezer, Chairman Ma,

341
00:20:36,910 --> 00:20:39,280
is making a fuss about catching
the hit-and-run driver himself.

342
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,380
Any ideas?

343
00:20:41,810 --> 00:20:44,110
A hit-and-run carries a prison sentence
of at least one year.

344
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:47,350
But a settlement could lead to a fine
or a suspended sentence.

345
00:20:48,290 --> 00:20:50,190
Do you have someone who'll do it?

346
00:20:51,490 --> 00:20:53,060
Is there anything money can't buy?

347
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,290
You know that as well as I do.

348
00:20:56,330 --> 00:20:59,900
Right. Pay someone to confess.

349
00:21:03,330 --> 00:21:05,200
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

350
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:09,770
Mom.

351
00:21:11,010 --> 00:21:12,080
Mom...

352
00:21:18,020 --> 00:21:19,920
(Premium Gift Set)

353
00:21:31,530 --> 00:21:34,430
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

354
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:49,510
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

355
00:21:49,580 --> 00:21:51,350
(Premium Gift Set)

356
00:21:54,150 --> 00:21:55,190
Mom.

357
00:21:56,190 --> 00:21:57,690
My poor mom.

358
00:21:58,460 --> 00:21:59,590
I missed you so much.

359
00:21:59,990 --> 00:22:02,530
Suk Hee likes cake.

360
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:04,530
Mom.

361
00:22:05,930 --> 00:22:09,200
Eat lots of your favorite cake.

362
00:22:10,770 --> 00:22:13,270
Seo Rin will be waking up soon.

363
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:16,040
And then the three of us
can go on a picnic.

364
00:22:16,870 --> 00:22:17,870
Okay?

365
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:22,650
I love you, Mom.

366
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:26,420
My poor mom.

367
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:35,030
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

368
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:10,290
Tae Pyung. Jang Mi's gone.

369
00:23:10,630 --> 00:23:14,360
I miss Jang Mi. Where did Jang Mi go?

370
00:23:14,530 --> 00:23:18,140
Where did my pretty Jang Mi go?

371
00:23:18,140 --> 00:23:19,240
Mom.

372
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:21,510
You're like a broken record.

373
00:23:22,570 --> 00:23:24,310
I'm tired of even answering you.

374
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:28,880
Jang Mi's gone.

375
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:31,280
Jang Mi is pretty.

376
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:34,420
Jang Mi...

377
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:38,520
Grandma, don't cry.
Bo Ra will sing you a lullaby.

378
00:23:38,890 --> 00:23:41,020
Okay, Bo Ra.

379
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:47,100
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

380
00:23:47,660 --> 00:23:49,100
That monster, Chae Hwa Young,

381
00:23:50,230 --> 00:23:52,470
tried to kill me all this time...

382
00:23:52,470 --> 00:23:54,340
to hide the fact
that Seo Rin and I were twins.

383
00:23:55,510 --> 00:23:56,510
Mom.

384
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:00,040
I promise I'll get you justice...

385
00:24:00,810 --> 00:24:02,310
for all the injustice
you and Dad suffered.

386
00:24:03,780 --> 00:24:07,450
I'll make Chae Hwa Young pay
for all she's done to our family.

387
00:24:08,420 --> 00:24:09,650
Until then,

388
00:24:10,390 --> 00:24:11,720
please just wait a little longer.

389
00:24:14,260 --> 00:24:15,830
I love you, Mom.

390
00:24:32,510 --> 00:24:35,510
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

391
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:43,250
(Premium Gift Set)

392
00:24:44,790 --> 00:24:46,020
I wonder who left this.

393
00:24:48,590 --> 00:24:50,730
It must've been Baek Ho. He's at it again.

394
00:24:51,190 --> 00:24:52,230
Honestly.

395
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:53,930
What? Me?

396
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:57,370
You think I'm the one who brought
the beef ribs and cake?

397
00:24:57,670 --> 00:24:59,400
Don't play dumb with me.

398
00:24:59,670 --> 00:25:02,770
You're just pretending because you think
we won't accept it from you.

399
00:25:02,910 --> 00:25:04,240
But it's fine.

400
00:25:04,510 --> 00:25:07,740
- I'll swallow my pride and enjoy it.
- But it wasn't me.

401
00:25:08,210 --> 00:25:11,480
- It really wasn't me.
- My mom's already digging in.

402
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:13,920
Hello?

403
00:25:14,550 --> 00:25:16,890
(Law Firm Leeho)

404
00:25:16,950 --> 00:25:18,050
That's weird.

405
00:25:19,990 --> 00:25:21,260
If it wasn't me, then who was it?

406
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,400
I'm pretty because I take after you, Mom.

407
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:30,730
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

408
00:25:31,430 --> 00:25:32,770
Jang Mi is so pretty.

409
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:36,210
My poor mom.

410
00:25:37,910 --> 00:25:39,940
Your accident...

411
00:25:40,810 --> 00:25:42,680
must have been Chae Hwa Young's doing.

412
00:25:44,850 --> 00:25:47,880
I can't believe she had to live like this
when she was perfectly normal.

413
00:25:49,890 --> 00:25:50,950
Mom...

414
00:25:51,490 --> 00:25:52,890
My poor mom.

415
00:25:55,490 --> 00:25:56,990
I had no idea,

416
00:25:58,260 --> 00:26:01,360
and I was grateful
to that monster, Chae Hwa Young.

417
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:42,640
You monster.

418
00:26:44,110 --> 00:26:45,780
With that kind, benevolent act of yours,

419
00:26:46,710 --> 00:26:48,810
you deliberately wormed your way
into our family.

420
00:26:49,310 --> 00:26:52,420
What have you done?

421
00:26:55,650 --> 00:26:57,620
- Seo Rin.
- You're wrong.

422
00:26:58,250 --> 00:27:00,660
I'm not Seo Rin. I'm Jang Mi.

423
00:27:01,260 --> 00:27:02,330
Oh Jang Mi.

424
00:27:02,930 --> 00:27:05,500
The same Oh Jang Mi you've been
trying so desperately to kill.

425
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:07,760
What did you say?

426
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:12,940
You killed my dad, didn't you?
Why did you kill him?

427
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:16,710
- Don't do this. Let me go.
- Tell me why you killed him.

428
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:19,210
Why did you have
my innocent father killed?

429
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:22,210
Manager Lee forced my father to drink
and then killed him.

430
00:27:22,210 --> 00:27:24,980
That was on your orders, wasn't it?

431
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:26,850
Please, let me live.

432
00:27:27,150 --> 00:27:29,020
Let go of me and talk.

433
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:32,260
Die!

434
00:27:32,260 --> 00:27:34,160
You had my father killed,

435
00:27:34,390 --> 00:27:35,660
so you deserve to die too.

436
00:27:35,930 --> 00:27:37,760
You're going to die just like he did!

437
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:39,730
Please, don't kill me.

438
00:27:59,250 --> 00:28:01,250
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
